00:49:03,607 --> 00:49:06,526
I was the one that asked you out today.

1043
00:49:07,361 --> 00:49:09,863
But what did you think of the date so far?

1044
00:49:09,947 --> 00:49:12,658
I was worried about
if you were having fun.

1045
00:49:17,496 --> 00:49:18,330
I'm sorry.

1046
00:49:22,334 --> 00:49:25,003
So, I'm glad you enjoyed it.

1047
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:30,425
Why are you looking away?

1048
00:49:30,926 --> 00:49:31,927
What's wrong?

1049
00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:34,805
What is it?

1050
00:49:35,305 --> 00:49:36,723
Hey. What is it?

1051
00:49:37,224 --> 00:49:39,101
What's going on? Come on.

1052
00:49:39,601 --> 00:49:41,311
What? Are you crying?

1053
00:49:42,229 --> 00:49:44,481
Are they good tears? Happy tears?

1054
00:49:45,065 --> 00:49:45,983
What's up?

1055
00:49:46,858 --> 00:49:50,028
What is it? Wait, really. What's going on?

1056
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:01,248
What's wrong?

1057
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:03,625
What is it?

1058
00:50:06,628 --> 00:50:07,462
I'm okay.

1059
00:50:07,963 --> 00:50:09,881
You don't look okay.

1060
00:50:14,344 --> 00:50:17,389
Well, at least during this trip,

1061
00:50:18,348 --> 00:50:21,685
I fell for the first girl I met

1062
00:50:22,185 --> 00:50:24,688
and went on two dates with her.

1063
00:50:25,188 --> 00:50:27,399
I gave her the Wish Letter
and came here today.

1064
00:50:27,899 --> 00:50:31,653
But I couldn’t make her happy
and ended up making her worried.

1065
00:50:32,154 --> 00:50:34,156
- How do I put it?
- That's not true.

1066
00:50:34,239 --> 00:50:35,073
Yeah.

1067
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:37,159
Just forget it.

1068
00:50:38,744 --> 00:50:41,371
You're okay with that?
You're just gonna forget it?

1069
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:46,710
I want to take you back to your hotel
and see you off until the end.

1070
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:51,673
But I don't feel anything from your end.

1071
00:50:53,050 --> 00:50:54,009
Feel what?

1072
00:50:54,843 --> 00:50:56,970
Affection or feelings.

1073
00:50:57,054 --> 00:50:58,013
I see.

1074
00:50:58,096 --> 00:51:01,558
So, I guess I don't need to
force myself to do all that.

1075
00:51:01,641 --> 00:51:02,601
Why?

1076
00:51:02,684 --> 00:51:05,729
- Why would you think that far?
- Of course I would.

1077
00:51:05,812 --> 00:51:07,147
Hey.

1078
00:51:07,939 --> 00:51:11,151
I'm sorry. I didn't mean it like…

1079
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:14,571
It's totally fine.
And it feels wrong to have you apologize.

1080
00:51:15,447 --> 00:51:16,448
It's okay.

1081
00:51:17,699 --> 00:51:19,034
So, why don't we

1082
00:51:20,327 --> 00:51:21,453
go back to Nice?

1083
00:51:23,246 --> 00:51:24,748
Okay.

1084
00:51:24,831 --> 00:51:26,583
I'm not "okay" at all.

1085
00:51:27,084 --> 00:51:27,918
Why?

1086
00:51:35,342 --> 00:51:36,468
I don't know.

1087
00:51:36,551 --> 00:51:39,638
- I don't get it myself either.
- Why don't you know?

1088
00:51:41,098 --> 00:51:44,643
- You would know…
- This is the loudest I've been this trip.

1089
00:51:46,645 --> 00:51:47,979
I really don't get it.

1090
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:51,066
What is this?

1091
00:51:52,025 --> 00:51:53,944
I really had fun

1092
00:51:55,487 --> 00:51:57,114
coming here with you.

1093
00:51:58,156 --> 00:52:00,075
But there were moments

1094
00:52:00,575 --> 00:52:01,993
when I was thinking,

1095
00:52:02,077 --> 00:52:07,791
"I wonder if he's having fun."

1096
00:52:07,874 --> 00:52:10,085
I wasn't exactly worried,

1097
00:52:10,710 --> 00:52:13,922
but I was wondering about that.

1098
00:52:14,756 --> 00:52:15,590
- Maybe.
- Okay.

1099
00:52:15,674 --> 00:52:18,635
After you wondered about it,
what would you do then?

1100
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:20,428
- What would I do?
- Yeah.

1101
00:52:20,512 --> 00:52:23,181
You wonder that,
but you just go about on your own

1102
00:52:24,432 --> 00:52:25,851
and let it slide?

1103
00:52:27,102 --> 00:52:28,186
And just watch?

1104
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:32,440
- But that's not for me to think about.
- Because you're the guest?

1105
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:33,692
Right?

1106
00:52:33,775 --> 00:52:36,194
I just figured
that's what you're thinking.

1107
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:40,365
We talked a bit during the date,
and you said, "I'll have fun!"

1108
00:52:40,866 --> 00:52:41,700
Yeah.

1109
00:52:41,783 --> 00:52:42,951
So…

1110
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:48,039
I thought you were thinking about
how to enjoy yourself.

1111
00:52:48,123 --> 00:52:49,833
To be honest,

1112
00:52:49,916 --> 00:52:55,463
it's hard to 1,000% enjoy myself
alone in a one-sided love.

1113
00:52:55,964 --> 00:52:59,843
Especially on a special trip like this.

1114
00:53:00,343 --> 00:53:04,264
I'm not the kind of person
who can make that happen.

1115
00:53:04,764 --> 00:53:05,599
Yeah.

1116
00:53:07,767 --> 00:53:10,103
This is probably the real me.

1117
00:53:10,604 --> 00:53:11,563
Yeah.

1118
00:53:11,646 --> 00:53:12,856
That's not true.

1119
00:53:12,939 --> 00:53:19,029
If you decide to enjoy
the moment at your maximum,

1120
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:21,281
you might be able to
let your date have fun too.

1121
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:26,161
For me, I feel that
if I'm not enjoying myself,

1122
00:53:26,244 --> 00:53:29,581
the other person won't enjoy it either.

1123
00:53:29,664 --> 00:53:34,294
So, I try to keep myself in a good mood.

1124
00:53:34,794 --> 00:53:36,046
That's how I think.

1125
00:53:41,509 --> 00:53:44,471
Please don't be so hard on yourself.

1126
00:53:48,975 --> 00:53:50,185
I had fun.

1127
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:52,854
I was just wondering how you felt.

1128
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:55,023
It's not that I didn't enjoy myself.

1129
00:53:55,523 --> 00:53:57,317
I really had fun.

1130
00:53:57,817 --> 00:54:01,321
I was just wondering if you had fun too.

1131
00:54:03,907 --> 00:54:06,409
You don't have to think so hard about it!

1132
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:14,084
Let's go back to Nice.

1133
00:54:14,167 --> 00:54:15,585
- Shall we?
- Yeah.

1134
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:19,005
Nice is cold too.

1135
00:54:19,506 --> 00:54:23,969
- Yeah, Nice is cold.
- It's freezing.

1136
00:54:24,719 --> 00:54:26,554
My hotel is this way.

1137
00:54:26,638 --> 00:54:27,639
Okay.

1138
00:54:27,722 --> 00:54:30,433
- See you.
- Yes, thank you. See you.

1139
00:54:30,517 --> 00:54:34,354
Tomorrow at 12:00 p.m.

1140
00:54:34,437 --> 00:54:37,941
I'll see you near the intersection
at train station number 15.

1141
00:54:38,024 --> 00:54:40,026
Then let's do the French <i>bisou</i>.

1142
00:54:42,821 --> 00:54:43,780
- See you.
- See you.

1143
00:54:43,863 --> 00:54:45,657
- Good night.
- Good night.

1144
00:54:52,163 --> 00:54:53,540
Maho is stylish.

1145
00:54:53,623 --> 00:54:55,458
That was very stylish of Maho.

1146
00:54:55,542 --> 00:54:56,418
So cool.

1147
00:55:00,005 --> 00:55:01,298
Trickle, trickle.

1148
00:55:03,341 --> 00:55:05,593
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1149
00:55:07,262 --> 00:55:09,931
KANAKA, 25, BRAND PRODUCER

1150
00:55:10,015 --> 00:55:12,100
This tastes so good!

1151
00:55:12,183 --> 00:55:15,186
NANAMI, 25, ACTOR

1152
00:55:15,270 --> 00:55:16,479
You were with him today?

1153
00:55:16,563 --> 00:55:19,816
Yeah. We went parasailing together.

1154
00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:23,320
I'm going to go parachuting on Day Nine.

1155
00:55:23,403 --> 00:55:24,571
What? Really?

1156
00:55:25,071 --> 00:55:26,156
With whom?

1157
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:27,407
With Yudai.

1158
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:28,783
Stop it.

1159
00:55:41,212 --> 00:55:42,547
To the right…

1160
00:55:57,854 --> 00:55:58,688
Dear Yudai,

1161
00:55:58,772 --> 00:56:00,732
I look forward to parachuting on Day Nine.

1162
00:56:00,815 --> 00:56:01,733
From Riko

1163
00:56:01,816 --> 00:56:03,318
I got you lemon soap.

1164
00:56:06,029 --> 00:56:08,948
What was it like
when you met him on Day Five?

1165
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:09,949
I mean, Day Six.

1166
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:11,785
I asked him if we could hold hands.

1167
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:13,912
That's so cute!

1168
00:56:14,412 --> 00:56:15,789
Do you hold hands with Sho?

1169
00:56:15,872 --> 00:56:16,915
No.

1170
00:56:16,998 --> 00:56:17,999
Why not?

1171
00:56:18,875 --> 00:56:22,087
I think I'm still too shy to do that.

1172
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:24,047
- I see.
- How about you, Nanami?

1173
00:56:24,130 --> 00:56:27,509
How are things with you and Kensuke?

1174
00:56:27,592 --> 00:56:31,054
It's hard to open up and be honest.

1175
00:56:31,137 --> 00:56:32,347
- You?
- Yeah.

1176
00:56:32,430 --> 00:56:34,516
He asked me

1177
00:56:34,599 --> 00:56:38,561
if I hesitated in choosing
who to give my Wish Letter to.

1178
00:56:38,645 --> 00:56:39,479
And?

1179
00:56:39,562 --> 00:56:41,940
I didn't hesitate at all.

1180
00:56:42,023 --> 00:56:46,194
I wanted to act sweet and let him know

1181
00:56:46,277 --> 00:56:49,989
that I've had feelings for him all along.

1182
00:56:50,490 --> 00:56:52,158
But I was like, "I didn't hesitate."

1183
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:54,285
Oh, I get what you mean.

1184
00:56:54,786 --> 00:56:55,620
And,

1185
00:56:56,246 --> 00:56:57,872
maybe it's just me,

1186
00:56:58,790 --> 00:57:01,793
but I felt like
an awkward silence filled the air.

1187
00:57:02,419 --> 00:57:05,255
Maybe you can just tell him all that.

1188
00:57:05,338 --> 00:57:08,341
That you're not good at being honest.

1189
00:57:09,175 --> 00:57:10,218
Yeah.

1190
00:57:10,301 --> 00:57:13,138
Wouldn't giving him
the Wish Letter convey a message?

1191
00:57:13,221 --> 00:57:14,431
Oh, yeah.

1192
00:57:15,014 --> 00:57:15,849
That's true.

1193
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:27,777
KENSUKE, 24, COMEDIAN

1194
00:57:31,114 --> 00:57:31,948
Dear Yudai,

1195
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:34,701
I don't know what time
I'll be free on Day Eight.

1196
00:57:34,784 --> 00:57:36,703
I'd like you to wait for me at Margaux.

1197
00:57:36,786 --> 00:57:38,746
But don't push yourself!
Rest when you can!

1198
00:57:38,830 --> 00:57:39,664
From Nanami

1199
00:58:00,852 --> 00:58:02,270
Huh? Why?

1200
00:58:03,438 --> 00:58:04,689
Why?

1201
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:06,441
You startled me.

1202
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:10,695
Your cough gave you away.

1203
00:58:10,778 --> 00:58:13,239
- What? You knew it was me?
- Yeah.

1204
00:58:17,410 --> 00:58:18,828
Why are you here?

1205
00:58:19,621 --> 00:58:21,539
- What's that?
- For you.

1206
00:58:21,623 --> 00:58:24,042
Oh! Thank you.

1207
00:58:26,294 --> 00:58:28,129
- Open it later.
- Okay.

1208
00:58:34,302 --> 00:58:36,429
I didn't think you'd be here.

1209
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:39,432
Wait, no. That's not it.

1210
00:58:41,226 --> 00:58:42,727
Why are you crying?

1211
00:58:55,406 --> 00:58:56,908
You didn't think I'd be here?

1212
00:58:58,076 --> 00:58:59,536
I didn't mean… Wait.

1213
00:58:59,619 --> 00:59:01,871
That's not it.

1214
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:06,459
Hold on.

1215
00:59:08,336 --> 00:59:09,254
It's okay.

1216
00:59:11,256 --> 00:59:12,799
She's crying so hard.

1217
00:59:12,882 --> 00:59:16,302
I think she really had a hard time.

1218
00:59:17,345 --> 00:59:18,429
It was pretty bad.

1219
00:59:18,513 --> 00:59:19,681
Pretty bad?

1220
00:59:20,431 --> 00:59:23,309
It feels like my feelings

1221
00:59:23,393 --> 00:59:25,478
aren't getting through at all.

1222
00:59:25,562 --> 00:59:28,690
No matter what I say,
she brushes it off with,

1223
00:59:28,773 --> 00:59:30,858
"It's fine! You're overthinking it!"

1224
00:59:31,359 --> 00:59:33,236
And like, "Let's be happy!"

1225
00:59:33,319 --> 00:59:35,488
She treats it lightly.

1226
00:59:35,572 --> 00:59:38,324
That really got to me.

1227
00:59:38,408 --> 00:59:39,993
I mean,

1228
00:59:40,618 --> 00:59:45,415
I had pretty much decided
to stick with one girl until the end.

1229
00:59:45,498 --> 00:59:49,168
But I don't want to waste
the rest of my days here.

1230
00:59:49,252 --> 00:59:51,170
Do you have anybody else in mind?

1231
00:59:51,254 --> 00:59:52,589
- No.
- No?

1232
00:59:53,089 --> 00:59:54,299
No. But…

1233
00:59:55,633 --> 01:00:00,763
- I have no chance with Mimi anymore.
- It was that bad?

1234
01:00:00,847 --> 01:00:02,890
- Yeah.
- Really?

1235
01:00:02,974 --> 01:00:05,393
I mean, I came all the way to France.

1236
01:00:05,893 --> 01:00:07,604
I don't know

1237
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:10,440
how to spend the rest of my time.

1238
01:00:10,523 --> 01:00:12,066
- I see.
- Yeah.

1239
01:00:13,151 --> 01:00:16,696
This is definitely an incident.

1240
01:00:16,779 --> 01:00:18,573
Yes. An incident indeed.

1241
01:00:18,656 --> 01:00:20,199
There's a criminal element.

1242
01:00:20,283 --> 01:00:21,784
There's no criminal element.

1243
01:00:21,868 --> 01:00:24,078
There's absolutely no criminal element.

1244
01:00:24,162 --> 01:00:27,373
Aru is too serious.

1245
01:00:27,999 --> 01:00:29,667
He said it from the start.

1246
01:00:29,751 --> 01:00:31,294
- Just one person.
- "Die for you."

1247
01:00:31,377 --> 01:00:33,421
- "Die for you."
- He can die for that person.

1248
01:00:33,504 --> 01:00:35,548
He wants to meet that kind of person.

1249
01:00:35,632 --> 01:00:38,885
For Aru, Mimi is fun to be with.

1250
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:43,598
But knowing he's not her only option
gave him some major inner turmoil.

1251
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:47,602
She was kind to Sho too.
She's kind to everyone.

1252
01:00:47,685 --> 01:00:48,519
Aru knows that.

1253
01:00:48,603 --> 01:00:50,688
He liked her knowing that fact.

1254
01:00:50,772 --> 01:00:52,398
But the more she encouraged him,

1255
01:00:52,899 --> 01:00:56,778
the more he might have wondered

1256
01:00:56,861 --> 01:00:59,447
if she was saying
the same thing to everyone.

1257
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:01,199
He felt he wasn't her number one.

1258
01:01:01,282 --> 01:01:03,743
After all that mental exhaustion,

1259
01:01:03,826 --> 01:01:05,620
<i>she saw Atsushi smiling at her.</i>

1260
01:01:05,703 --> 01:01:09,332
<i>- Of course she would hug him.</i>
<i>- She would definitely hug him and cry.</i>

1261
01:01:09,415 --> 01:01:11,250
What if you were in Mimi's shoes, Kyoko?

1262
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:14,253
I'm not good at being affectionate,

1263
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:16,547
but that would definitely make me happy.

1264
01:01:16,631 --> 01:01:20,510
- I don't mean to spoil the mood.
- Yes?

1265
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:23,721
- What is it?
- I don't mean to rain on your parade.

1266
01:01:23,805 --> 01:01:25,306
Isn't Atsushi being unfair?

1267
01:01:25,807 --> 01:01:27,016
It wasn't unfair.

1268
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:29,018
What was unfair about that?

1269
01:01:29,102 --> 01:01:30,103
It's like,

1270
01:01:30,186 --> 01:01:32,313
the hare ended up winning just like that.

1271
01:01:32,397 --> 01:01:35,441
Right. You looked forward to
the other ending.

1272
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:39,737
We were worried about how it would be
if things went well with Aru.

1273
01:01:40,238 --> 01:01:42,657
It just so happened to not work out.

1274
01:01:42,740 --> 01:01:44,659
- We couldn't do anything.
- Just listen.

1275
01:01:44,742 --> 01:01:47,120
Let's say Mimi
had enjoyed her date with Aru,

1276
01:01:47,203 --> 01:01:49,831
but she couldn't stop
thinking about Atsushi,

1277
01:01:49,914 --> 01:01:52,875
so she ended up saying,
"I'll head back first."

1278
01:01:52,959 --> 01:01:54,836
And Atsushi was waiting for her then.

1279
01:01:54,919 --> 01:01:57,046
- I'd say, "Well done, Atsushi!"
- He deserved it.

1280
01:01:57,130 --> 01:02:00,925
But while Aru and Mimi's date went south,
he was just swimming.

1281
01:02:01,718 --> 01:02:02,927
Why would you care?

1282
01:02:03,010 --> 01:02:04,262
He swam and waited.

1283
01:02:04,345 --> 01:02:07,265
He was like, "How are things going?
Everything okay?"

1284
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:10,476
Everything went well.
We all knew he would give her the letter.

1285
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,980
He had the Wish Letter
for Day Eight in the first place.

1286
01:02:14,063 --> 01:02:17,650
It wasn't like he strategically got
the letter by switching with somebody.

1287
01:02:17,734 --> 01:02:19,569
- He just had it.
- Yeah.

1288
01:02:19,652 --> 01:02:22,530
He was lucky.
Of course he would go to the hotel.

1289
01:02:22,613 --> 01:02:24,615
He needed to deliver the letter by hand.

1290
01:02:24,699 --> 01:02:28,619
That happened to coincide perfectly
with Mimi's situation.

1291
01:02:28,703 --> 01:02:29,537
That's right.

1292
01:02:29,620 --> 01:02:34,917
When Mimi cried, I bet Atsushi thought,
"She wanted to see me that badly."

1293
01:02:35,001 --> 01:02:36,544
- I see.
- But remember?

1294
01:02:36,627 --> 01:02:38,588
He believes in fate more than anybody.

1295
01:02:38,671 --> 01:02:41,132
- You're right!
- It was that power.

1296
01:02:41,215 --> 01:02:44,510
This was the result
of Atsushi believing in fate.

1297
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:45,553
Maybe you're right.

1298
01:02:47,221 --> 01:02:51,225
Atsushi is the one who's moving
most genuinely according to fate.

1299
01:02:51,309 --> 01:02:53,019
- Yeah.
- That's why things work out.

1300
01:02:53,102 --> 01:02:54,353
- This is fate too.
- Right.

1301
01:02:54,437 --> 01:02:57,815
That's probably why
Atsushi doesn't overthink

1302
01:02:57,899 --> 01:03:00,109
the gaps between himself and reality.

1303
01:03:00,193 --> 01:03:02,153
- He looks straight forward.
- He follows fate.

1304
01:03:02,236 --> 01:03:06,824
So he doesn't get upset
about not being able to meet her,

1305
01:03:06,908 --> 01:03:09,577
or wonder what it means
that she’s with Aru right now.

1306
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:12,955
Some try to carve their path
with the power of reality,

1307
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:14,373
like Nanami, Tohko, and Aru.

1308
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:17,376
That's why they sometimes
get knocked down in the process.

1309
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:18,419
You're right.

1310
01:03:18,503 --> 01:03:20,880
Aru wasn't supposed to do a recon.

1311
01:03:20,963 --> 01:03:24,675
- Scouting places was the wrong move.
- Recon is the opposite of fate.

1312
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:27,678
That's true. You're absolutely right.

1313
01:03:27,762 --> 01:03:30,973
- It's almost the same as googling things.
- Right.

1314
01:03:31,057 --> 01:03:32,183
- I see.
- You're right.

1315
01:03:32,266 --> 01:03:35,019
Aru made a handmade smartphone.

1316
01:03:35,102 --> 01:03:35,978
I don't get that.

1317
01:03:36,479 --> 01:03:38,022
That was an awful metaphor.

1318
01:03:38,105 --> 01:03:40,191
- He made a handmade smartphone.
- Handmade?

1319
01:03:40,274 --> 01:03:43,694
They can't use smartphones.
It's no time to be making one.

1320
01:03:43,778 --> 01:03:45,404
What's with that metaphor?

1321
01:03:45,488 --> 01:03:48,574
- It's not okay.
- They need to follow their instincts.

1322
01:03:50,076 --> 01:03:52,620
I passed my letter
to Kensuke for Day Five.

1323
01:03:53,120 --> 01:03:56,582
He said he was going to
hand his letter to Nanami.

1324
01:03:57,208 --> 01:04:00,044
He had already decided back then.

1325
01:04:00,127 --> 01:04:01,379
- Really?
- Yeah.

1326
01:04:02,547 --> 01:04:04,715
- He said he'll hand his to me?
- Yeah.

1327
01:04:04,799 --> 01:04:07,051
He's a fun person to be with.

1328
01:04:07,134 --> 01:04:07,969
- Yeah.
- Definitely.

1329
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:10,429
It's not the same feeling
I have for Yudai,

1330
01:04:10,513 --> 01:04:14,976
but I told him I wasn't sure
what it meant to like someone as a person.

1331
01:04:15,059 --> 01:04:16,018
He said, "Thank you."

1332
01:04:16,519 --> 01:04:19,105
"But I will pass
my Wish Letter to Nanami."

1333
01:04:19,605 --> 01:04:21,649
- What?
- He said that then and there.

1334
01:04:21,732 --> 01:04:25,361
He must really like you.

1335
01:04:26,362 --> 01:04:28,281
- Your date tomorrow…
- I'll have fun!

1336
01:04:28,364 --> 01:04:30,658
Just enjoy your date tomorrow to the max.

1337
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:34,829
Is this…

1338
01:04:35,454 --> 01:04:36,497
What is it?

1339
01:04:36,581 --> 01:04:38,124
It's nothing.

1340
01:04:39,709 --> 01:04:40,543
Well…

1341
01:04:46,507 --> 01:04:47,341
Huh?

1342
01:04:49,343 --> 01:04:52,138
I think maybe I like him.

1343
01:04:52,221 --> 01:04:53,764
Am I in love?

1344
01:04:54,265 --> 01:04:55,308
You are.

1345
01:04:56,267 --> 01:04:57,435
I think you are.

1346
01:04:57,518 --> 01:05:01,314
Am I in love? I don't know.

1347
01:05:02,189 --> 01:05:04,525
Do you like him as a romantic partner?

1348
01:05:04,609 --> 01:05:06,235
Or as a person?

1349
01:05:06,319 --> 01:05:08,613
It's difficult to differentiate the two.

1350
01:05:08,696 --> 01:05:10,781
That's probably why you're confused.

1351
01:05:10,865 --> 01:05:13,784
It's the same for me with Sho.

1352
01:05:15,995 --> 01:05:17,788
I haven't asked about her feelings.

1353
01:05:18,289 --> 01:05:20,458
- You haven't?
- No. I haven't asked yet.

1354
01:05:20,541 --> 01:05:22,585
I'm not sure how she thinks about me.

1355
01:05:22,668 --> 01:05:26,213
I'm gonna tell her I like her tomorrow.

1356
01:05:26,297 --> 01:05:27,173
Really?

1357
01:05:27,673 --> 01:05:30,384
- Seriously?
- I'm gonna tell her I like her tomorrow.

1358
01:05:30,468 --> 01:05:31,886
Not Day Ten, but tomorrow?

1359
01:05:32,386 --> 01:05:33,804
I plan to tell her tomorrow.

1360
01:05:34,305 --> 01:05:37,141
He's so cool! He's decided already.

1361
01:05:37,224 --> 01:05:39,185
Did Sho star in <i>IWGP?</i>

1362
01:05:39,810 --> 01:05:41,354
- Yeah.
- He's like King.

1363
01:05:41,437 --> 01:05:43,356
What happens if one confesses their love?

1364
01:05:43,439 --> 01:05:45,816
There are no rules regarding that.
It could be…

1365
01:05:45,900 --> 01:05:48,069
They could start going out?

1366
01:05:48,152 --> 01:05:51,697
We only have the no smartphones rule
and the Wish Letter rules.

1367
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:52,615
Wow!

1368
01:05:52,698 --> 01:05:55,743
It's amazing
how quickly things are moving.

1369
01:05:55,826 --> 01:05:56,911
So true!

1370
01:05:56,994 --> 01:06:00,122
- Isn't it pretty amazing?
- It definitely is.

1371
01:06:01,165 --> 01:06:01,999
Here.

1372
01:06:04,502 --> 01:06:06,295
- For me?
- Tomorrow…

1373
01:06:08,214 --> 01:06:11,425
I think you're the only one for me,
so I'm giving this to you.

1374
01:06:11,509 --> 01:06:12,802
Thank you.

1375
01:06:12,885 --> 01:06:13,886
I hoped for this.

1376
01:06:15,096 --> 01:06:17,348
- I hoped for this the most.
- Good.

1377
01:06:18,015 --> 01:06:19,183
Can I have it?

1378
01:06:19,266 --> 01:06:20,351
It's for you.

1379
01:06:20,434 --> 01:06:21,811
It'll be more fun than today.

1380
01:06:21,894 --> 01:06:22,812
Okay.

1381
01:06:23,896 --> 01:06:26,524
Is there something I should know?
How should I dress?

1382
01:06:26,607 --> 01:06:28,693
- Bring your swimwear.
- Swimwear?

1383
01:06:28,776 --> 01:06:30,236
- Swimwear.
- What?

1384
01:06:30,945 --> 01:06:32,571
- My swimwear?
- Your swimwear.

1385
01:06:33,072 --> 01:06:34,323
- Bring it with you.
- Okay.

1386
01:06:34,824 --> 01:06:36,033
Did you think I'd be here?

1387
01:06:36,117 --> 01:06:37,410
- Huh?
- No?

1388
01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:39,870
I thought you would come,

1389
01:06:39,954 --> 01:06:42,456
but I didn't expect you to be here now.

1390
01:06:42,957 --> 01:06:44,959
I was surprised.

1391
01:06:45,459 --> 01:06:50,297
You were here when my head
was a bit overwhelmed.

1392
01:06:51,799 --> 01:06:54,802
- I felt relieved and tears poured out.
- That's good.

1393
01:06:56,804 --> 01:06:58,514
- Do I look ugly?
- You look pretty.

1394
01:07:02,518 --> 01:07:04,395
- Rest well today.
- Okay.

1395
01:07:04,478 --> 01:07:05,312
Here.

1396
01:07:10,276 --> 01:07:12,653
What did she say?

1397
01:07:12,737 --> 01:07:15,740
Did she say anything
about having feelings for someone?

1398
01:07:15,823 --> 01:07:16,657
No.

1399
01:07:16,741 --> 01:07:18,034
If not,

1400
01:07:18,117 --> 01:07:19,410
isn't that frustrating?

1401
01:07:20,494 --> 01:07:23,456
- Isn't it frustrating losing to Atsushi?
- Losing?

1402
01:07:23,539 --> 01:07:26,751
- It's not about winning or losing.
- He's taking her.

1403
01:07:29,670 --> 01:07:31,630
Let's take a look.

1404
01:07:35,885 --> 01:07:36,719
"Dear Mimi,

1405
01:07:36,802 --> 01:07:39,513
I want to spend Day Eight with you."

1406
01:07:39,597 --> 01:07:40,890
I can't stop smiling.

1407
01:07:40,973 --> 01:07:43,601
"You must be tired today. Rest well!"

1408
01:07:44,101 --> 01:07:46,562
"Let's have fun tomorrow! From Atsushi."

1409
01:07:46,645 --> 01:07:48,272
I'll definitely have fun.

1410
01:07:50,775 --> 01:07:51,942
It smells nice.

1411
01:07:54,820 --> 01:07:56,864
But if you've already chosen one person,

1412
01:07:57,364 --> 01:08:00,993
if I were you, I would stick
to my decision until the end.

1413
01:08:01,077 --> 01:08:03,037
- Yeah.
- I wouldn't wanna give up.

1414
01:08:03,120 --> 01:08:05,414
No girl would fall for you

1415
01:08:06,123 --> 01:08:08,292
when you're down like this.

1416
01:08:08,375 --> 01:08:12,171
I think Mimi would be attracted to you

1417
01:08:12,922 --> 01:08:16,258
if you continue to pursue her
without giving up.

1418
01:08:26,936 --> 01:08:28,854
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
